Wash and dry all produce. Place @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{1%cup}, a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{}, @Cumin{1/2%tsp}, @Dried Oregano{1/2%tsp} and a large pinch of @Salt{} in a #small pot{}. Cover pot and bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until meal is ready.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-low heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add onion and cook, tossing occasionally, until softened and starting to brown, about ~{5%minutes}.

While onion and rice cook, core, seed and thinly slice @Poblano Pepper{1}(cored, seeded, and thinly sliced). Finely mince @Garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Once onion is softened, add poblano to pan. Cook, tossing occasionally, until poblano is tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Toss in half the garlic and cook one minute more. Pour in @water{1/4%cup} and let simmer until just evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Pat @Sirloin Steak{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season with plenty of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}, then rub with remaining @Cumin{1/2%tsp} and @Dried Oregano{1/2%tsp}. Heat @Vegetable Oil{1%tbsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and let rest at least ~{5%minutes}.

While steak cooks, zest 1 tsp zest from @Lime{1}, then cut into quarters. In a #small bowl{}, mix @Sour Cream{4%tbsp}, a pinch of remaining garlic, half the lime zest, and a squeeze of lime juice. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture has a loose, drizzly consistency. Season to taste with @Salt{} and more lime juice.

Add remaining lime zest to rice in #pot{} and fluff with a #fork{}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Slice steak against the grain. Divide rice between plates, arrange steak on top, and add veggie mixture to the side. Dollop with crema.